-- Fairfield Sentry Sues to Recover $115 Million From Offshore Bank
-- B y   K a r e n   G u l l o
-- 2012-04-14T00:27:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-14/fairfield-sentry-sues-to-recover-115-million-from-offshore-bank.html
Fairfield Sentry Ltd. (FAISENI) , a feeder
fund that transferred $3.2 billion to  Bernard Madoff ’s firm,
sued Cayman Islands-based Atlantic Security Bank to recover $115
million it says were proceeds of the conman’s Ponzi scheme.  The case is Fairfield Sentry v. Atlantic Security Bank,
12-01550, U.S. Bankruptcy Court, Southern District New York
(Manhattan).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Gullo in San Francisco at   kgullo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Hytha at   mhytha@bloomberg.net . 